    title: "Irregular Preterite: Tener, Estar, Poder",
    grammar: "<b>Irregular Preterite: TENER, ESTAR, PODER</b><br><br>These verbs share a pattern: they use a special irregular stem + regular -ER preterite endings (without accent marks).<br><br><table class='conj-table'><tr><th>Verb</th><th>Stem</th><th>yo</th><th>tú</th><th>él</th><th>nosotros</th><th>ellos</th></tr><tr><td><b>TENER</b></td><td>tuv-</td><td>tuve</td><td>tuviste</td><td>tuvo</td><td>tuvimos</td><td>tuvieron</td></tr><tr><td><b>ESTAR</b></td><td>estuv-</td><td>estuve</td><td>estuviste</td><td>estuvo</td><td>estuvimos</td><td>estuvieron</td></tr><tr><td><b>PODER</b></td><td>pud-</td><td>pude</td><td>pudiste</td><td>pudo</td><td>pudimos</td><td>pudieron</td></tr></table><br><b>Examples:</b><br>Ayer <b>tuve</b> mucho trabajo. (Yesterday I had a lot of work.)<br>Nosotros <b>estuvimos</b> en el parque toda la tarde. (We were in the park all afternoon.)<br>Ella no <b>pudo</b> venir a la fiesta. (She couldn't come to the party.)<br>¿<b>Tuviste</b> tiempo para hacer la tarea? (Did you have time to do the homework?)<br>Ellos <b>estuvieron</b> muy ocupados. (They were very busy.)<br>Yo no <b>pude</b> dormir anoche. (I couldn't sleep last night.)",
