    title: "Irregular Preterite: Dar, Ver, Andar",
    grammar: "<b>Irregular Preterite: DAR, VER, ANDAR</b><br><br><table class='conj-table'><tr><th>Verb</th><th>yo</th><th>tú</th><th>él</th><th>nosotros</th><th>ellos</th></tr><tr><td><b>DAR</b></td><td><b>di</b></td><td>diste</td><td><b>dio</b></td><td>dimos</td><td>dieron</td></tr><tr><td><b>VER</b></td><td><b>vi</b></td><td>viste</td><td><b>vio</b></td><td>vimos</td><td>vieron</td></tr><tr><td><b>ANDAR</b></td><td><b>anduve</b></td><td>anduviste</td><td><b>anduvo</b></td><td>anduvimos</td><td>anduvieron</td></tr></table><br><b>Note:</b> Dar and Ver use the -ER/-IR preterite endings but without accent marks. Dar uses the endings but the stem is just d-.<br><br><b>Examples:</b><br>Yo le <b>di</b> un regalo a mi madre. (I gave a gift to my mother.)<br>¿Qué te <b>dieron</b> ellos? (What did they give you?)<br>Anoche <b>vi</b> una película muy buena. (Last night I saw a very good movie.)<br>Nosotros <b>vimos</b> a Juan en el parque. (We saw Juan in the park.)<br>Yo <b>anduve</b> por el centro comercial toda la tarde. (I walked around the mall all afternoon.)<br>Ellos <b>anduvieron</b> buscando un apartamento. (They walked around looking for an apartment.)",
