    title: "Shadowing & Speaking Practice",
    grammar: "<b>Shadowing & Speaking Practice Techniques</b><br><br>Shadowing helps improve pronunciation, rhythm, and fluency.<br><br><b>Technique 1 – Repeat after audio:</b><br>Listen to native speaker → pause → repeat exactly with same intonation.<br><br><b>Technique 2 – Mirror reading:</b><br>Read text aloud while listening to native audio simultaneously.<br><br><b>Technique 3 – Self-recording:</b><br>Record yourself speaking → compare to native → adjust.<br><br><b>Tongue twisters for pronunciation (trabalenguas):</b><br>• Tres tristes tigres tragan trigo en un trigal.<br>• El perro de San Roque no tiene rabo porque Ramón Ramírez se lo ha robado.<br>• Pepe pide pipas, pipas pide Pepe.<br><br><b>Common conversation starters:</b><br>¿Qué tal? / ¿Cómo estás? (How are you?)<br>¿Qué hay de nuevo? (What's new?)<br>¿Cómo te va? (How's it going?)<br>Cuéntame de tu día. (Tell me about your day.)<br>¿Has oído lo de...? (Have you heard about...?)<br><br><b>Practice phrase:</b> Repite en voz alta: 'Tres tristes tigres tragan trigo en un trigal.'",
    vocab: { theme: "Speaking Practice", words: [{es:"en voz alta",en:"out loud"},{es:"grabar",en:"to record"},{es:"escuchar",en:"to listen"},{es:"repetir",en:"to repeat"},{es:"imitar",en:"to imitate"},{es:"pronunciar",en:"to pronounce"},{es:"entonación",en:"intonation"},{es:"ritmo",en:"rhythm"},{es:"fluidez",en:"fluency"},{es:"trabalenguas",en:"tongue twister"}] },
