    title: "Review – Pronouns & Commands",
    grammar: "<b>Pronouns & Commands Final Review</b><br><br><b>DO pronouns:</b> me, te, lo/la, nos, os, los/las<br><b>IO pronouns:</b> me, te, le, nos, os, les<br><b>Double:</b> IOP + DOP (le/les → se before lo/la/los/las)<br><br><b>Commands summary:</b><br><br><table class='conj-table'><tr><th></th><th>Affirmative</th><th>Negative</th></tr><tr><td>Tú</td><td>Habla (indicative)</td><td>No hables (subj)</td></tr><tr><td>Ud.</td><td>Hable (subj)</td><td>No hable (subj)</td></tr><tr><td>Uds.</td><td>Hablen (subj)</td><td>No hablen (subj)</td></tr><tr><td>Nosotros</td><td>Hablemos (subj)</td><td>No hablemos (subj)</td></tr></table><br><b>Pronouns with commands:</b><br>Affirmative: Attach to end (add accent): Dímelo. / Cómprenselo.<br>Negative: Before verb: No me lo digas. / No se lo compren.<br><br><b>Final practice:</b><br>Dígame cómo llegar al museo. (Tell me how to get to the museum – Ud.)<br>No te preocupes, todo va a salir bien. (Don't worry, everything will be fine – tú)<br>Sentémonos y hablemos del problema. (Let's sit down and talk about the problem.)",
